      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FARROH JOE (2) deserves a win after placing in his last five outings, some of those coming behind some smart juveniles. Has had two months off but was kept up to the mark with a trial and should get his chance from a low draw. LATHER IN GOLD (7) proved too good in scoring last start by 3.5 metres at Shepparton. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw but she is lightly raced with upside and has recorded a win and a placing in two tries at this distance so with even luck she can go right on with the job. JASPER JAY (5) showed pleasing improvement when third in his second outing at Shepparton. Could progress further. SMOKEN HEAVEN (1) has had some tough draws of late but was runner-up in a Melton trial since last seen and he is better served by the ace draw.",
